UT_Stub_RegisterReturnType, UT_Stub_RegisterContextWithMetaData, UT_ExecuteBasicHandler, UT_Stub_GetReturnValuePtr — The static call graph shows unit-test stub/handler functions associated with OS_SelectMultiple. In test/instrumented builds these stubs can be injected around the call (or expand to additional control-flow) causing additional returns, aborts or other control transfers that could render code unreachable. To be certain there is no unreachable code in the target function across real and test builds, these stub-related symbols must be analyzed as well.
